Brandon Dubinsky scored the go-ahead
goal in the second period to give the  New York Rangers  their
fourth straight National Hockey League win, a 3-1 victory over
the  Pittsburgh Penguins .  Brad Richards tied the score at 1-1 in the first period
last night after Ben Lovejoy gave the Penguins the lead at 5:43
at Consol Energy Center in Pittsburgh.  Derek Stepan added the third goal for the Rangers at 1:20
of the final period.  The Rangers (26-9) are atop the Eastern Conferenceâ€™s five-
team Atlantic Division ahead of the Philadelphia Flyers (23-11)
and Penguins (21-14). They also top the Eastern Conference with
